The paper deals with a distributed optimization problem in which servers need to visit a set of requests while minimizing the total distance travelled. This problem involves several aspects of computer science, including distributed computing (cs.DC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The absence of communication among the servers also suggests a focus on distributed computing and algorithms.
